- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a self-triggered control scheme for nonlinear systems.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also likely as the paper proposes a computational approach for generating approximations of isochronous manifolds.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible category as the proposed scheme can be applied to control robotic systems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes an algorithm for generating approximations of isochronous manifolds.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also less likely but possible as the paper uses approximations of isochronous manifolds to derive the regions for the self-triggered control scheme, which could potentially be applied in machine learning applications.
